{"source_key":"sha256-77a8d0a023ee41ad7912180250238aff","record_index":2104,"record_hash":"sha256:8c5e47313aeefe1f6c892ad9c2a5faa95738823f216c4b5e2e272e3b835e8ac7","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.108Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- **Fix now**: Unbounded `tool_input` can dump huge/sensitive payloads into GitMeta. Tool results are capped, but tool call inputs are stored whole after redaction only: [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:111), [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:254). Cap or summarize tool inputs too.\\n\\n- **Fix now**: Public API is wider than current callers need. `lib.rs` exports session/read/related APIs that only tests use right now: [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12), [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:98). Keep these `pub(crate)` until `but` or API code actually consumes them.\\n\\n- **Fix now**: `associate_session` lost the nice error context the rest of `gitmeta` has. Failures from open/set just bubble raw: [write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:214). Add context for opening GitMeta and associating the target/session.\\n\\n- **Document**: Environment capture intentionally stores repo-sensitive metadata: paths, branch names, full commit IDs, review/change IDs: [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:50), [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:64), [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:84), [environment.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:394). That may be fine, but since `sync_metadata` can push it, the privacy boundary needs an explicit note.\\n\\n- **Document**: Capture/read paths are whole-log/list oriented. Capture reads the full transcript into memory: [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:18). Timeline reads the full transcript list and scans it for needed hashes: [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:391). Fine for POC, but call out the expected transcript/session size.\\n\\n- **Ignore**: The module split itself is sane. Shared private wire/storage structs in `mod.rs`, read/write split, and tests under `gitmeta/tests.rs` are boring in the good way.\\n\\nValidation: `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes, 42 tests.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.108Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}